<TITLE> Most Filipinos dissatisfied with Arroyo: poll </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MANILA, April 14 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Philippine President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo's approval ratings have slipped to the worst in over two years, the country's leading pollster said on Monday. The Social Weather Stations agency said 54 percent of respondents in a poll conducted in the last week of March were dissatisfied with Arroyo, while only 27 percent were satisfied. The net satisfaction rating, rounded off to minus 26, is Arroyo's worst performance in the quarterly polls since a score of minus 30 in December 2005. Arroyo, who is facing calls from the opposition to resign over corruption and kickbacks scandals, is however not seen to be in any danger and will most likely remain in office until 2010, when her tenure ends, political analysts have said. Her spokesman said Arroyo was not worried about the poll showing. "Political reform and tough choices take their toll on President Arroyo's approval rating just as they have for other leaders around the world," said Ignacio Bunye in a statement. "The most important thing for the President is results not poll numbers." Despite a string of reverses in opinion surveys, she is supported by the military and has an overwhelming majority in the House of Representatives. Many in the powerful Catholic church also support h
